crowdstrike red team intern 


What You'll Do

Assist in the design, implementation, and execution of adversarial simulations, threat & technique research, product measurement, reporting, and metrics.

Report results, including mitigation strategies, for both management and technical audiences.

Assist in developing and improving product efficacy.

What You'll Need

A passion for using your offensive security skills to stop breaches.

A rising junior, senior, or graduate-level computer science or cybersecurity student, graduating between December 2024 - August 2025

Experience with security assessment frameworks and tools (Examples: Metasploit, NMAP, Cobalt Strike, Empire, Mimikatz, etc.) is preferred.

Understanding of security methodologies, technologies, and best practices.

Windows / Linux / Mac operating system experience (Cloud is a bonus).

Experience in automation and scripting of applications and systems is preferred.

Experience in one or more high-level programming languages (C++, Rust, .Net, Go, Python, Java, etc.) is preferred.

